 for bestpractices and # File Upload & Management

## Overview
Build a secure, scalable File Upload & Management system to support uploading, storing, versioning, previewing, and securely serving drawings, images, and attachments for Archject. This system powers:

- Signed uploads/downloads to AWS S3 (or Cloudinary direct uploads as an optional alternative)
- Server-side malware/virus scanning pipeline
- Thumbnail and PDF preview generation (via Lambda or server workers)
- Fine-grained access controls and temporary signed URLs
- Integration with Drawings & Specs Library, Decision Detail Page, and Create Decision Page
- Versioning history, thumbnails, quick-attach to decisions, and export artifacts

The implementation must align with Archject’s UX and design system, ensuring a calm, readable interface, clear visual hierarchy, and reliable data integrity across devices and client access.

---

## components to Build

1) File Storage Service (Backend Core)
- Purpose: Store and manage file objects with versioning, access control, and provenance.
- Storage: AWS S3 (preferred) with lifecycle rules; optional Cloudinary direct upload path as alternative.
- Features:
  - Object metadata: projectId, fileId, version, filename, mimeType, size, ownerUserId, createdAt, expiry (if signed URL is temporary)
  - Versioning: keep previous versions accessible; expose API to fetch specific version or latest
  - Access control: per-file ACLs; ability to generate time-limited signed URLs for download or upload
  - Triggers: on upload, trigger malware scan, thumbnail generation, and optional PDF generation
  - Thumbnails/previews: support for image thumbnails and PDF previews (via Lambda or server worker)
  - Lifecycle: auto-archive/delete non-active versions after policy window (configurable)

2) Ingestion & Security Pipeline
- Malware/virus scanning: integrate with scanning service (e.g., ClamAV, AV, or a managed scanner). Ensure scans run asynchronously and block or quarantine uploads on detection.
- Validation: MIME type sniffing, file size limits, allowed extensions per project policy.
- Thumbnails & Preview generation: 
  - Images: generate thumbnail at multiple sizes (e.g., 256px, 64px)
  - Drawings: generate thumbnail for quick attachment previews
  - PDFs: generate first-page thumbnail and optional text rendering for previews
- Signaling: publish status events (SCANNED, CLEAN, INFECTED, THUMBNAIL_READY, PREVIEW_READY)

3) Drawings & Specs Library Page (Frontend)
- Central repository per project
- Features:
  - Upload new drawings/spec files with versioning
  - View library with thumbnail grid/list; sort by date, version, name
  - Version history panel for each file
  - Quick attach to decisions (attach file to a decision card)
  - Preview pane for images and PDFs (inline)
  - Client-side search and filters (by name, type, version, date)
- UI: card-based and grid/list toggle; thumbnails; status badges; action menu (download, share, versioned view)

4) Decision Detail Page (Frontend)
- Full Decision Card view
- Features:
  - Visual comparison of options (side-by-side thumbnails/previews)
  - Comments thread with threaded responses
  - Approval status badge (Approved, Pending, Rejected)
  - History timeline with file attachments and actions
  - Attachments management: view, download, replace, and remove
  - Actions: share link (no-login or token-based), export decision pack (PDF/ZIP), create follow-up task
- UX: emphasis on visual decision-making and easy access to attachments and history

5) Create Decision Page (Frontend)
- Multi-step flow (modal or page)
- Steps:
  - Template selection: choose from predefined templates or create custom
  - Options: add decision options (images/drawings, descriptions, pricing, materials)
  - Attachments: attach drawings/specs from library or uploaded files
  - Recipients: select client recipients for reminders and approvals
  - Reminder Schedule: set automatic reminders and due dates
- UX: progress indicators, inline validation, and contextual help

6) API Layer (Backend)
- Authentication & Authorization
  - Bearer token/session-based auth; per-user access to the project space
  - Role-based access: Viewer, Editor, Approver, Admin
- File APIs
  - Upload: signed POST URL generation or direct upload (multipart)
  - Download: signed GET URL with expiry
  - Preview/Thumbnail: signed URLs for preview endpoints
  - Versioning: endpoints to fetch file versions, promote a version, restore
  - Attachments: attach/detach to decisions
- Drawings & Specs Library APIs
  - CRUD for library items; version history retrieval
  - Attach to decision: API to attach a file reference to a decision
- Decision APIs
  - Create decision (from multi-step flow)
  - Update decision (options, attachments, recipients)
  - Decision detail retrieval (with attachments and history)
- Webhook & Events
  - Notify frontend or workspace services on file scans, thumbnail ready, new version, or new attachment

7) Database Models (Data Layer)
- Projects
- Users
- Files
  - id, projectId, fileName, mimeType, size, version, isLatest, uploadedBy, uploadDate, s3Key, etag, scanStatus, thumbnailS3Key, previewUrl, expiry
  - versionHistory: separate table to track per-file versions (fileId, version, s3Key, uploadedAt, uploadedBy, mimeType, size)
- Decisions
  - id, projectId, title, status, createdAt, dueDate, approvedAt
- DecisionOptions
  - id, decisionId, label, description, assetFileId (attachment)
- Attachments
  - decisionId, fileId, role (attachment type)
- Recipients & Reminders
- ActivityLog
  - track actions: created decision, attached file, approved, reminder sent, export, share

8) Frontend Components & Pages
- File Library Grid/List with thumbnail previews
- File Preview Panel (image/PDF)
- Thumbnail generation display
- Attachment Picker integrated with decision creation/edit flows
- Signed URL display and copy/share utilities
- Multi-step modal for Create Decision
- Decision Card View with side-by-side comparison layout
- Activity Timeline component

9) Utilities & Helpers
- Signed URL generator (server-side)
- File type validators and MIME-type mapping
- Image/PDF thumbnail renderer or thumbnail URL generator
- PDF export pack assembler (gathers decision content and attachments into a PDF/ZIP)
- Validation utilities for forms and inputs
- Retry/backoff logic for uploads and scans

---

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Frameworks: React (with hooks) or a modern alternative; state management with Redux/Context
- UI Components: Reusable components aligned to design system (cards, buttons, inputs, selects, modals, sidebars)
- Accessibility: ARIA labels, keyboard navigation, proper focus states
- Networking: Fetch/Axios with retry logic; handle signed URLs
- Performance: Lazy load thumbnails; pagination/infinite scroll for large libraries
- Upload UX: 
  - Drag-and-drop zone
  - Show progress bars, chunked uploads for large files
  - Real-time status (Uploaded, Scanned, Ready)
- Preview: Inline previews for images; embedded PDF viewer or canvas-based thumbnail; fallback viewer for unsupported types
- Error handling: Clear error messages, retry options, and degraded mode for offline/slow networks
- Security: Do not expose raw S3 keys; always use signed URLs for client operations

### Backend
- Language/Stack: Node.js (NestJS/Express) or Python (FastAPI) or Java (Spring) depending on project baseline
- API Design: RESTful endpoints with versioned routes; consistent response schema; thorough Swagger/OpenAPI docs
- Storage Integration:
  - AWS SDK v3 integration for S3 operations
  - Optional Cloudinary integration path with direct uploads
- Scanning & Thumbnails:
  - Lambda-based workers or in-service background jobs (e.g., using SQS/SNS or a queue)
  - Image processing via Sharp or equivalent; PDF thumbnail via PDF renderer
- Security:
  - JWT or OAuth-based authentication
  - Per-file signed URL generation with short TTL (e.g., 15 minutes)
  - Access control checks on every request
- Data Integrity:
  - Database migrations; data seeding for projects/users
  - Audit trails for file version changes and decision updates
- Observability:
  - Logging, metrics, and error tracking (e.g., Sentry)
  - Job status dashboards for scans and thumbnail generation

### Integration
- Linking components:
  - File storage service exposes APIs for upload/download/versions
  - Library and Decision pages fetch file metadata and thumbnails via API
  - Decision Create flow uses library attachments and uploads to populate attachments
  - Event bus or webhook system to propagate updates (new version, scan result, reminder)
- Consistency:
  - Ensure data consistency between file version history and the visible latest version
  - Ensure signed URLs are refreshed when expired and access controls are enforced

## User Experience Flow

- Uploading a File
  1) User opens Drawings & Specs Library or Decision Create flow
  2) Drag-and-drop or click to select a file
  3) Client shows upload progress; files queued for upload
  4) Backend stores the file; malware scan starts automatically
  5) If clean, thumbnail and preview are generated; status updated to Ready
  6) User sees the file in library with thumbnail; option to attach to decisions

- Attaching to a Decision
  1) User opens a Decision (Detail or Create)
  2) User selects “Attach” and picks files from the library
  3) System creates a link between the file version (latest or chosen version) and the decision
  4) Attachments appear in the Decision’s Attachments section; user can download the file or view preview

- Viewing a Decision
  1) Decision detail shows options in a side-by-side comparison, comments, and status
  2) Attachments are accessible via thumbnails; user can share or export the decision pack
  3) User can create a follow-up task from the decision actions

- Creating a Decision
  1) User starts Create Decision flow
  2) User picks a template (or custom)
  3) User adds options and attaches drawings/specs from the library
  4) User selects client recipients and sets reminder schedule
  5) On finish, a new Decision is created with all attachments and related files stored in library

## Technical Specifications

Data Models: (Core shapes)
- File
  - id, projectId, fileName, mimeType, size, version, isLatest, uploadedBy, uploadedAt, s3Key, thumbnailKey, previewUrl, scanStatus, accessControlList, expiresAt
- FileVersion
  - id, fileId, version, s3Key, uploadedAt, uploadedBy, mimeType, size
- Decision
  - id, projectId, title, status, createdAt, dueDate, approvedAt, createdBy
- DecisionAttachment
  - id, decisionId, fileId, role (attachment_type)
- LibraryItem
  - id, projectId, fileId, metadata (tags, description), version, createdAt
- User
  - id, name, email, role, permissions
- ActivityLog
  - id, type, subjectId, details, timestamp, userId

API Endpoints (examples; adapt to stack)
- POST /api/v1/projects/{projectId}/files/sign-upload-url
  - body: { fileName, mimeType, size, folderPath }
  - returns: { uploadUrl, fileId, signedHeaders }
- POST /api/v1/projects/{projectId}/files
  - upload completed event payload; creates file record; initiates scan
- GET /api/v1/projects/{projectId}/files/{fileId}
  - returns file metadata
- GET /api/v1/projects/{projectId}/files/{fileId}/versions
  - returns version history
- GET /api/v1/projects/{projectId}/files/{fileId}/download-url?version={version}
  - returns signed URL for download
- GET /api/v1/projects/{projectId}/libraries
  - list library items with pagination
- POST /api/v1/projects/{projectId}/libraries/upload
  - alternative endpoint for direct signed URL upload
- POST /api/v1/projects/{projectId}/decisions
  - create decision (from multi-step flow)
- GET /api/v1/projects/{projectId}/decisions/{decisionId}
  - retrieve decision with attachments
- POST /api/v1/projects/{projectId}/decisions/{decisionId}/attachments
  - attach file to decision
- POST /api/v1/projects/{projectId}/decisions/{decisionId}/export
  - export decision as PDF/ZIP
- POST /api/v1/projects/{projectId}/scans/trigger
  - enqueue scan job (if separate)

Security
- Authentication: JWT/OAuth2; access restricted by project and user roles
- Authorization: Verify project membership and role for every operation
- Signed URLs: Short TTL (e.g., 15 minutes) for read/write operations
- Virus scanning: Reject and quarantine files with malware; provide remediation steps
- Data retention: Enforce lifecycle rules; archive or delete according to policy

Validation
- File type/size restrictions per policy
- Required fields for creation and attachments
- Consistent versioning rules (increment version correctly; mark isLatest)
- All endpoints return predictable success/error formats with codes and messages

Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Users can upload large drawings and attachments with progress feedback; files are stored in S3 with version history
- [ ] Uploaded files pass malware scanning; only clean files become visible with thumbnails/previews
- [ ] Thumbnails and first-page PDF previews are generated and accessible via signed URLs
- [ ] Quick attach to decisions works; attachments display in Decision Detail with correct version
- [ ] Create Decision flow supports multi-step process, including attachment of library items and reminder scheduling
- [ ] Export of a Decision generates a packaged artifact (PDF/ZIP) containing decision content and attachments
- [ ] All UI components align with the design system and pass accessibility checks

UI/UX Guidelines
Apply the project’s design system:
- Clean, calm workspace background (#F7F7F9) with cards on white panels
- Primary actions use accent color (#0052CC); secondary actions are ghost or outline
- Consistent typography; H1 ~28px, H2 ~22px, body 15–16px
- 12-column grid with 24–32px gutters; generous whitespace
- Card design: soft shadows, rounded corners, borders in #E5E7EB
- Sidebar navigation with clear active states; top bar with minimal borders
- Status indicators using color codes: success (#10B981), warning (#F59E42), error (#EF4444)
- Interactive elements have smooth transitions and accessible focus states

Visual Style
- Maintain high readability and clarity; minimize decorative elements
- Use thumbnails and visual cues to aid quick decision-making
- Ensure responsive behavior for desktop and mobile clients

---

 Connected Pages
- Page_Drawings_Library: central repository with versioning, thumbnails, and quick attach to decisions
- Page_Create_Decision: multi-step modal or page to create a Decision Card with options, attachments, recipients, reminders
- Page_Decision_Detail: full decision view with visual comparisons, comments, approvals, history, attachments, and actions (share, export, follow-up task)

 Connected APIs
- AWS S3 (File Storage): object storage for large drawings, attachments, and export artifacts; signed URLs; lifecycle rules
- Optional: Cloudinary direct upload path if preferred

