=== TASK ===
# File Upload & Management

## Overview
Build a secure, scalable File Upload & Management system to support uploading, storing, versioning, previewing, and securely serving drawings, images, and attachments for Archject. This system powers:

- Signed uploads/downloads to AWS S3 (or Cloudinary direct uploads as an optional alternative)
- Server-side malware/virus scanning pipeline
- Thumbnail and PDF preview generation (via Lambda or server workers)
- Fine-grained access controls and temporary signed URLs
- Integration with Drawings & Specs Library, Decision Detail Page, and Create Decision Page
- Versioning history, thumbnails, quick-attach to decisions, and export artifacts

The implementation must align with Archject’s UX and design system, ensuring a calm, readable interface, clear visual hierarchy, and reliable data integrity across devices and client access.

---

## components to Build

1) File Storage Service (Backend Core)
- Purpose: Store and manage file objects with versioning, access control, and provenance.
- Storage: AWS S3 (preferred) with lifecycle rules; optional Cloudinary direct upload path as alternative.
- Features:
  - Object metadata: projectId, fileId, version, filename, mimeType, size, ownerUserId, createdAt, expiry (if signed URL is temporary)
  - Versioning: keep previous versions accessible; expose API to fetch specific version or latest
  - Access control: per-file ACLs; ability to generate time-limited signed URLs for download or upload
  - Triggers: on upload, trigger malware scan, thumbnail generation, and optional PDF generation
  - Thumbnails/previews: support for image thumbnails and PDF previews (via Lambda or server worker)
  - Lifecycle: auto-archive/delete non-active versions after policy window (configurable)

2) Ingestion & Security Pipeline
- Malware/virus scanning: integrate with scanning service (e.g., ClamAV, AV, or a managed scanner). Ensure scans run asynchronously and block or quarantine uploads on detection.
- Validation: MIME type sniffing, file size limits, allowed extensions per project policy.
- Thumbnails & Preview generation: 
  - Images: generate thumbnail at multiple sizes (e.g., 256px, 64px)
  - Drawings: generate thumbnail for quick attachment previews
  - PDFs: generate first-page thumbnail and optional text rendering for previews
- Signaling: publish status events (SCANNED, CLEAN, INFECTED, THUMBNAIL_READY, PREVIEW_READY)

